n independent criteria for fitness. Darwin wrote extensively about artificial selection in pigeons, in which the breeders' choice was the criterion for fitness. (Many novel breeds of pigeon have been created this way.) Artificial selection has been practiced extensively by plant and animal breeders. Here too, survival is not the criterion for fitness, productivity is."Robert H Tamarin, (1996) "Principles of Genetics" (5th ed), p571.Where has it been shown? How is it used to make predictions about species chances of survival for the future?
