I am rather passionate on this subject. My mother died at the age of 58 in 1963, after several years of declining health.After working through specialist after specialist we finally were given an explanation which made sense, and has since been confirmed in many other cases.I could have said "Penicillin" killed my mother, but this would be inaccurate. After WWII penicillin was the "wonder drug", dispensed for all sorts of things, in fairly moderate dosages. It was many years before we learned that a modest dosage kills off MOST of the bacteria, leaving behind a bunch of tough little survivors who continue to breed.The doctor explain that colonies of bacteria had evolved within my mother's both that nothing available at the time could totally exterminate.The offfical cause of death was emphysema, a bit surprising since she had never smoked a cigarette in her life."Survival of the fittest" in this case means the penicillin-resistant bacteria."Evolution" means the creation of new populations, immune to the wonder drug. "Increase in information" means the reduction in the "noise" of the penicillin-susceptble genes, and a consequent increase in useable information.Go back and read your Shannon if you doubt it.Will some creationist point out the errors in the above? But if you do, make sure you protect your identity.After all these years it still hurts.IzzyemoticonXBanghead
